  The Nigeria Olympic Committee (NOC) in collaboration with the Olympic Solidarity is organizing a two-day seminar for sports journalists in Nigeria.  The Seminar is scheduled to hold tomorrow and Wednesday, July 7 with the theme “Reporting compelling story ideas that provide a solution to a hurting world” and participants will also look at how to cover a multi-sports event using the Olympic Games as a guide.  The virtual cum physical seminar will have facilitators such as Benny Bonsu, Director-Daily Content Olympic Channels; Ikeddy Isiguzo former editorial board chairman of Vanguard Newspaper as well as, Sports Content Consultant, Deji Omotoyinbo and Adetola Badekale, Senior Content Producer, SuperSport Nigeria.  The seminar will be declared open by the President of NOC, Habu Gumel.  